      "content": "wow ok so you're basically saying they're a necessity then? i mean, i get the worker side of it, but isn't there a massive argument that unions just drive up costs for consumers and make it harder for businesses to hire people in a flexible way? feels like you're taking a pretty hard stance on this.",
